member.summary:
A set of bit flags that describe the state of the DFS root or link;

the state of the DFS namespace root cannot be changed.

One  flag is set, and one DFS_VOLUME_FLAVOR flag is set.

Permission to create an instance of the resource (such as a file);

data can be written to the resource as the resource is created.

Win32: ACCESS_CREATE = 0x00000004

The SECURITY_INFORMATION data type identifies the object-related security information being set or queried.
            This security information includes:
              The owner of an object;
              The primary group of an object;
              The discretionary access control list (DACL) of an object;
              The system access control list (SACL) of an object;
